# LLM Stack Layout

This repository uses a provider-agnostic structure:

- Common workflow docs in `docs/`
- Common skill logic in `.agent-stack/skills/`
- Thin model wrappers under model-specific directories

## Canonical Files

- `docs/workflows/apply-common.md`
- `docs/multi-agent-setup.md`
- `.agent-stack/skills/apply-common.md`
- `.agent-stack/skills/pr-review.md`
- `.agent-stack/skills/post-apply-checklist.md`
- `.agent-stack/stack.json`

## Model Wrapper Paths

- Codex: `.codex/skills/*/SKILL.md`
- Claude: `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`
- Gemini: `.agent/skills/*/SKILL.md`

Wrappers should remain minimal and delegate behavior to common docs/files.

## Why This Layout

- One source of truth for process changes
- Minimal drift between models
- Easy bootstrap for new repositories
